Mix chicken, mayonnaise, celery, almonds and onion salt. Cut baguette lengthwise in half. Arrange lettuce on bottom half of baguette; top with tomato slices. Spread chicken mixture over tomatoes; top with avocado dip. Sprinkle with green onions. Top with remaining baguette half. Cut diagonally into 8 slices. *To Toast Almonds: Bake uncovered in ungreased shallow pan in a 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) oven for about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally, until golden brown. Or cook in ungreased heavy skillet over medium low heat for 5 to 7 minutes, stirring frequently until browning begins, then stirring constantly until golden brown.